I also seem to be hitting this issue when the model is an enum. e.g.

```
type MyEnum string
...
const (
	// MyEnumCONNECTED captures enum value "CONNECTED"
	MyEnumCONNECTED MyEnum = "CONNECTED"
	// MyEnumDISCONNECTED captures enum value "DISCONNECTED"
	MyEnumDISCONNECTED MyEnum = "DISCONNECTED"
)
...
type PutStateParams struct {
	BodyParam models.MyEnum

	timeout    time.Duration
	Context    context.Context
	HTTPClient *http.Client
}
...
```
is also missing the SetBodyParam from the WriteToRequest.

Looks like there are some body parameters which are not being identified by this line in the template?
```
  {{ if or .Schema.IsInterface .Schema.IsStream (and .Schema.IsArray .Child) (and .Schema.IsNullable (not .HasDiscriminator)) }}if {{ .ValueExpression }} != nil {
```
Different type, but same cause as #1339

issue.title: Client parameters don't set body when model is an enum
issue.body:
## Problem statement

If the client body is an enum, the body doesnt get serialised by WriteToRequest.

## Swagger specification

```yaml
swagger: '2.0'
info:
  version: "1.0.0"
  title: "Test enum serialisation"
paths:

  /example:
    put:
      parameters:
      - name: "something"
        in: "body"
        description: "PUT enum example"
        required: true
        schema:
          $ref: '#/definitions/MyEnum'
      responses:
        202:
          description: "PUT OK"
        500:
          description: "Error"

definitions:

  MyEnum:
    type: "string"
    enum:
    - SOMEVALUE
    - SOMEOTHERVALUE
```

## Steps to reproduce

`swagger generate client -f ./swagger.yaml`

Note that put_example_responses.WriteToRequest() never calls r.SetBodyParam().

## Environment
swagger version: master
go version: 1.10.2 
OS:  osx

## Fix
Looks like the following in the template needs to include enums:
```
  {{ if or .Schema.IsInterface .Schema.IsStream (and .Schema.IsArray .Child) (and .Schema.IsNullable (not .HasDiscriminator)) }}if {{ .ValueExpression }} != nil {
```

body:
it looks like somebody broke our master compile by not adding the required dependencies to our vendor.
We'll fix it. @stevecookform3 we want the most default go toolchain (go get, go test ./..., etc) to work on go-swagger, thanks for letting us know.
